28
00:01:13.759 --> 00:01:15.839
You see, one must clearly differentiate.

29
00:01:16.159 --> 00:01:17.959
When I move like this, it is very different from

30
00:01:18.519 --> 00:01:20.259
this movement at the level of my liver.

31
00:01:21.339 --> 00:01:22.219
So, if I want

32
00:01:22.639 --> 00:01:24.139
to rework a tissue, I restore it

33
00:01:24.209 --> 00:01:29.869
to its motility, and its functional strength, its functional strength is there, you

34
00:01:29.869 --> 00:01:31.409
see, that's where

35
00:01:31.409 --> 00:01:35.229
it will recover, and that's the work we do: returning to this tissue so that

36
00:01:35.229 --> 00:01:41.369
it can reorganize, regain its mobility, its motricity, you

37
00:01:41.369 --> 00:01:42.349
understand, it's

38
00:01:42.349 --> 00:01:47.049
always following the movement, but here you need the fulcrums, and after sensing the movement

39
00:01:47.049 --> 00:01:51.769
in your hand, I don't treat an organ, I treat an environment.

40
00:01:53.298 --> 00:01:59.658
But sometimes, my action can be on motility, mobility,

41
00:01:59.798 --> 00:02:00.378
